## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

---

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 6 |
| **High** | 1 |
| **Medium** | 1 |

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. Every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called (giving you that 95% line coverage), but almost nothing is actually *verified*. These tests cannot fail when bugs are introduced — which is exactly why bugs ship to production.

---

### 🔴 Critical — False Confidence

#### 1. Coverage Touching (Systemic)

The entire class follows a pattern of calling every method with no or trivial assertions, in declaration order. This inflates coverage without verifying behavior.

**Affected tests (no assertion at all):**

| Test Method | Line |
|---|---|
| `AddProduct_Works` | 17 |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` | 33 |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` | 39 |
| `GetProductCount_Works` | 64 |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` | 69 |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` | 85 |

These tests will pass even if the methods silently do nothing.

**Fix — example for `AddProduct_Works`:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_ProductIsRetrievableBySku()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);

    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var retrieved = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", retrieved?.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, retrieved?.Price);
}
```

**Fix — `UpdatePrice_Works`:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_ChangesProductPrice()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));

    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated?.Price);
}
```

**Fix — `RemoveProduct_Works`:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void RemoveProduct_ProductNoLongerRetrievable()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));

    _catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");

    Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
}
```

**Fix — `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works`:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void ApplyBulkDiscount_ReducesPricesByFraction()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 100m));

    _catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);

    Assert.AreEqual(90m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")?.Price);
}
```

---

#### 2. Trivial `IsNotNull` Assertions Masking Missing Verification

